Notes.
Williamson (
1915
) includes an illustration of epiproct in posterior view (reproduced in 

Lencioni 
2005

), in which the medial lobe is comparatively larger and strongly widened distally, almost with an inverted T shape, not observed in the specimens studied or in the drawings of von Ellenrieder & Garrison (
2008
).
